{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bdf6a03d-0388-4eb1-978e-63ab3814acb9","content":"The template is **functional but not fully publish-ready**. Here's what I found:\n\n**✅ Good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author` — all present\n- `sourceName` for project renaming\n- `classifications` and `tags` properly set\n- `Framework` parameter with valid choices\n\n**⚠️ Missing / Recommended for NuGet:**\n\n| Field | Impact |\n|---|---|\n| `$schema` | No schema URL — IDE validation/autocomplete won't work |\n| `description` | **Missing entirely** — critical for NuGet discoverability |\n| `groupIdentity` | Recommended when you may publish related templates |\n\n**Verdict:** Add at minimum a `description` field and the `$schema` before publishing. Without a description, the template will be hard to find and understand on NuGet. Would you like me to add those fields?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f0a85118-eaf6-4e92-a17f-cd1d26fa8f03","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. Let me check what's required for a .NET template to be published to NuGet.\n\nKey fields for a template.json:\n1. `$schema` - recommended but not strictly required\n2. `identity` - ✅ present\n3. `name` - ✅ present\n4. `shortName` - ✅ present\n5. `sourceName` - ✅ present (used for name replacement)\n6. `author` - ✅ present\n7. `classifications` - ✅ present\n8. `tags` - ✅ present with language and type\n\n\n9. `preferNameDirectory` - not present but optional\n10. `groupIdentity` - missing, recommended for NuGet\n11. `precedence` - optional\n12. `description` - **MISSING** - this is important for discoverability on NuGet\n\nSo I'm seeing a few gaps that would affect NuGet publishing: the `$schema` field would help with validation, but more critically, the template lacks a `description` field which is essential for discoverability, and `groupIdentity` is recommended if you're planning to publish multiple related templates. The `defaultValue` for Framework is set to \"net9.0\" which is appropriate, and `preferNameDirectory` is optional so that's not a concern.","outputTokens":627},"id":"132e51a7-19af-4c06-bd6f-04dc7639f2f3","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:40:57.867Z","parentId":"7953f8d5-9c64-456a-8763-937a922851ba"}
